**Abstract:**
Major essay dated September 1, 1997 titled "What to exist means and what inwardness signifies" opening with key Kierkegaard quotation on the misunderstanding between speculation and Christianity. Develops argument that faith was mistaken for speculative knowledge rather than practical knowledge terminating in action. Includes extensive analysis of Aquinas on enunciative vs. performative speech acts, critique of statements as pictures, and examination of Aristotle on rhetoric as discourse appealing to participants rather than disinterested spectators.

**AI Recommendation:** Central theoretical essay linking Kierkegaard to practical knowledge thesis; precedes 97-OCT series.

